	<div id="tribute-info">
		
		<h2 id="headline">	<br>Here's a Tribute Info About Albert Einstein's life: </h2>
		
	<ul><li style="padding-left:10px;">1879
	<br>Born in Germany ,Ulm.</li>
	<li>Aged 12
	<br>Einstein picked up a book on geometry and read it cover to cover. </li>
	<li>Aged 15
	<br>The family moved to Milan, Italy.</li>
	<li>1896 
	<br>Einstein renounced his German citizenship to avoid military conscription.</li>
	<li>1900
	 <br>Became a Swiss citizen and published his first scientific paper.
	</li>
	<li>1903
		<br> Married Mileva Maric and had two sons before divorcing several years later.
	</li>
	<li>
	1905 <br>Had completed his PhD entitled "A New Determination of Molecular Dimensions".</li>
	<li>
		1909<br>
		 He was given a post at the University of Zurich.</li>
<li>
	1911<br>Offered the post of full-professor at the Charles-Ferdinand University in Prague.
</li>
<li>1914
	<br> Returned to Germany,appointed director of the Kaiser Wilhelm Institute for Physics(1914-1932).
	</li>
<li>1916
	<br>General Theory of Relativity.
</li>
<li>1921
<br>Awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics.</li>
<li>
	1951 <br>Offered the position as President of Israel, but declined.
</li> 
<li>1955
	<br> Died at the age of 76.
</li>
<blockquote>
	<em>"School failed me, and I failed the school. It bored me. The teachers behaved like Feldwebel (sergeants). I wanted to learn what I wanted to know, but they wanted me to learn for the exam."
	<div>--Albert Einstein</em></div>
</blockquote>
